	<doc for="CodeLabeledStatement">
		<summary>
			<para>Represents a labeled statement or a stand-alone label.</para>
		</summary>
		<remarks>
			<para><see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeLabeledStatement"/> represents
   a label and optionally, an associated statement. A label can be used to indicate the
   target of a <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeGotoStatement"/>.</para>
			<para> The <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeLabeledStatement.Statement"/> property is optional. To
create only a label, leave the <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeLabeledStatement.Statement"/> property uninitialized. </para>
			<note type="note">
   Not all languages
   support <see langword="goto"/> statements and labels, so you should test
   wheter a code generator supports <see langword="goto"/>
   
   statements and labels by calling
   the <see cref="System.CodeDom.Compiler.ICodeGenerator.Supports"/> method with the <see cref="System.CodeDom.Compiler.GeneratorSupport.GotoStatements"/> flag.
</note>
		</remarks>
		<example>
			<para>The following example code demonstrates use of a <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeGotoStatement"/> and a <see cref="System.CodeDom.CodeLabeledStatement"/> to redirect program flow.</para>
			<codelink SampleID="CodeGotoStatementExample" SnippetID="2"/>
		</example>
		<seealso cref="System.CodeDom.CodeGotoStatement"/>
	</doc>
